Set-up

Data Overview

OTU tables

Taxonomy assigned using SINTAX algorithm (USEARCH v11)
Reference database: most current UNITE UNITE USEARCH/UTAX release for eukaryotes

  • version no 9.0, release date 2023-07-18

  • taxon group: All eukaryotes

  • location: https://dx.doi.org/10.15156/BIO/2938084

  • citation: Abarenkov, Kessy; Zirk, Allan; Piirmann, Timo; Phnen, Raivo; Ivanov, Filipp; Nilsson, R. Henrik; Kljalg, Urmas (2023): UNITE USEARCH/UTAX release for eukaryotes. Version 18.07.2023. UNITE Community. https://doi.org/10.15156/BIO/2938084

All EDGE samples have been excluded
ITS OTU table rarefied to 10,116 seqs/sample

Fungal (ITS) Dataset:

  • 6,749 OTUs
  • 509 samples
  • 731 unique genera detected, inc. Darksidea

Available metadata

Note that numeric metadata has been mean standardized.

Sampling Variables:

  • Grass host (n=5)
    • ANGE (Andropogon gerardii / Big bluestem)
    • SCSC (Schizachyrium scoparium / Little bluestem)
    • BOER (Bouteloua eriopoda / Black grama)
    • BOGR (B. gracilis / Blue grama)
    • BUDA (B. dactyloides / Buffalograss)
  • Grassland type (n=4)
    • desert, shortgrass, mixed grass, and tallgrass
  • Site (n=21)
  • GPS coordinates - latitude and longitude
  • Longitudinal Gradient (n=4)
    • North, North Central, South Central, South
  • Latitudinal Bin (n=3)
    • East, Middle, West
  • Elevation (in meters)

Climate Data:

  • GDD = growing degree days (determined over 3- and 30-year windows and in 2015)
  • ppt = mean annual precipitation (determined over 3- and 30-year windows and in 2015)
    *Data from PRISM Climate Group 2019 (Oregon State University)

Edaphic Variables:

  • ammonium (NH4+)
  • nitrate (NO3)
  • SOM (via LoI)
  • phosphorous (total P)
  • pH
  • soil_moisture = percentage by weight of water in soil (by sample, Rudgers et al.called this a climate variable)
    *soils combined within each Grass Host x Site combination

Plant Traits:

  • avg_SLA: specific leaf area
  • avg_SRL: specific root length
    • Large values of specific leaf area (SLA) and specific root length (SRL) reflect large plant investment in resource acquisition; small values indicate investment in plant tissue longevity
  • herbivory_perc: average site level damage estimate for herbivory, averaged over all species and individuals at the site; could be used to indicate herbivory pressure at the site level
    • ranges from 1:17

OTU-level relative abundance

Relative abundance of each OTU were averaged across all samples for this table.

This dataset contains 3 OTUs belonging to genus Darksidea.

At the OTU/species-level, all Darksidea OTUs were classified as uncl_Darksidea.

Mean and sd of Darksidea OTUs abundance across all samples:

  • OTU5613: 0.019 0.09%
  • OTU7431: 0.00017 0.003%
  • OTU9749: 0.0087 0.05%
    • Global sum: 0.028%

Genus-level relative abundance

Relative abundance of each OTU were averaged across all samples for this table.

This dataset contains 3 OTUs belonging to genus Darksidea.

At the species-level, all Darksidea OTUs were classified as uncl_Darksidea.

Across all samples, Darksidea had an average relative abundance of 0.028 0.11%.

Metadata variables impacting presence of Darksidea OTUs

Methods: For discrete metadata factors (e.g., Grass Host, Site), calculating occurrence for Darksidea OTUs by factor level and assessing significance of Occurrence ~ Factor via Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test (KW). For continuous metadata variables, I have converted the Darksidea OTU table to presence/absence, and assessed significance via a one-way ANOVA. All statistical tests in this section are single-term only. All continuous metadata variables have been mean standardized with the exceptions of elevation, latitude, and longitude.

  • Furthermore I calculated the variance explained by each variable

    • Kruskal-Wallis: \(\eta^2\) (effect size, essentially equivalent to \(R^2\)) using \(\eta\)\(p^2 = (F * dfn)/(F * dfn + dfd)\), given \(F(dfn, dfd)\)=\(\eta^2/(k-1)\). Because these are single term-based statistics and consequently, no other variable accounts for variance in the dependent variable, \(\eta\)\(p\) equals \(\eta^2\).
    • ANOVA: traditional \(R^2\) as calculated using sum of squares from the regression / total sum of squares

Darksidea OTU occurrence frequency significantly influenced by

Sampling Variables:

  • Site: (KW; \(\eta^2\) = 85.95, p-value < 2.2e-16, \(\chi^2\) = 2986)
  • Grassland type: (KW; \(\eta^2\) = 70.84, p-value = 1.05e-266, \(\chi^2\) = 1232)
  • Grass host: (KW; \(\eta^2\) = 69.94, p-value = 1.45e-253, \(\chi^2\) = 1177)
  • Latitudinal Bin: (KW; \(\eta^2\) = 20.1, p-value = 2.405e-27, \(\chi^2\) = 127)
  • Longitudinal Gradient: (KW; \(\eta^2\) = 8.53, p-value = 5.19e-11, \(\chi^2\) = 47.36)
  • Elevation (in meters): (AOV; \(R^2\) = 8.22, p-value = 4.36e-11)
  • Latitude: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 5.87, p-value = 3.13e-08)
  • Longitude: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 4.87, p-value = 4.97e-07)

Climate Data:

  • GDD = growing degree days: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 9.19, p-value = 2.81e-12)
  • ppt = mean annual precipitation: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 5.57, p-value = 7.23e-08)

Edaphic Variables:

  • soil_moisture: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 2.35, p-value = 0.00053)
  • ammonium: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 1.75, p-value = 0.00275)
  • nitrate: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 1.75, p-value = 0.00275)
  • phosphorous: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 1.45, p-value = 0.0065)
  • SOM (via LoI): NS
  • pH: NS

Plant Traits:

  • avg_SRL: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 7.27, p-value = 6.28e-10)
  • herbivory_perc: (AOV; \(R^2\) = 1.28, p-value = 0.0107)
  • avg_SLA: NS
